### Runtime Round 58 - ErrorHandling complete semantics
# Covers rollback, customWithRollback, customWithoutRollback, continue, RestCall latestHttpResponse,
# ErrorEvent rethrow, recursion guard, Loop/CallMicroflow propagation, trace output.errorHandling, and run errorHandlingSummary.
# Command:
#   npx tsx scripts/verify-microflow-error-handling-runtime.ts
# Expected JSON path checks:
# - $.data.session.trace[*].output.errorHandling.mode in ["rollback","customWithRollback","customWithoutRollback","continue"]
# - $.data.session.trace[*].output.errorHandling.transactionRolledBack=true for rollback/customWithRollback
# - $.data.session.trace[*].output.errorHandling.transactionRolledBack=false for customWithoutRollback/continue
# - $.data.session.trace[*].output.errorHandling.errorHandlerFlowId is present for custom handlers
# - $.data.session.trace[*].variablesSnapshot.$latestError exists only inside error handler frames
# - $.data.session.trace[*].variablesSnapshot.$latestHttpResponse exists only for RestCall custom handler frames
# - $.data.session.errorHandlingSummary.handledErrorCount / continuedErrorCount / rollbackCount reflect terminal status
# - $.data.session.output.errorHandlingSummary is present on successful handled/continued runs

